This paper is about natural language processing and machine learning, specifically about discourse relation sense classification. The use of long short-term memories (LSTM) and neural networks are common techniques in these fields, which suggest that the paper could belong to several sub-categories. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category, as it specifically deals with natural language processing. cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories, as they cover the use of machine learning techniques in various applications. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category, as it covers the use of neural networks. Finally, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category, but still possible, as it covers the use of neural networks in image and video analysis, which could be relevant to the paper's use of distributed representations.
